title: I Will Follow You Into The Dark chords
author: I Will Follow You Into The Dark – Death Cab for Cutie
song_information: [Intro] [Verse] F (F-C Root note going) Love of mine, Dm (D-A Root note going) Someday you will die Bb (strumming) But I will be close behind I will follow, you into the dark F (F-C Root note going) No blinding light Dm (D-A Root note going) Or tunnels to gates of white Just our hands clasped so tight Waiting for, the hint of a spark [Chorus] If heaven and hell decide, that they both are satisfied Illuminate the "no's", on their vacancy signs If there's no one beside you, when your soul embarks Bb Bbm F (Begin F-C root again) Then I will follow you into the dark [Verse] F (F-C root note going) Catholic school Dm (D-A root note) As vicious as roman rule I got my knuckles bruised By a lady in black F (F-C root note) Dm Bb And I held my tongue as she told me, "son, fear is the heart of love." So I never went back [Chorus] If heaven and hell decide, that they both are satisfied Illuminate the "no's", on their vacancy signs If there's no one beside you, when your soul embarks Bb Bbm F (Begin F-C root again) Then I will follow you into the dark [Verse] You and me, have seen everything to see From Bangkok to Calgary And the soles of your shoes Are all worn down, the time for sleep is now But it's nothing to cry about Because we'll hold each other soon, in the blackest of rooms [Chorus] If heaven and hell decide, that they both are satisfied Illuminate the "no's", on their vacancy signs Dm If there's no one beside you, when your soul embarks Bb Bbm F (run down to Dm on D string) Then I will follow you into the dark Then I will follow you into the dark ************************************************************************************* This song is from the upcoming release, "Plans" which is coming August 30th. I have a copy already and thought I would do those looking for the chords when it's released a service. It's a great, sparse little folk song that emphasizes the bottom half of the chords and strums mostly on the upbeats. The way this is done is by picking the bottom two notes of the chord on the downbeats of the verses. For example, with the F chord, it's played something like this, but the upper half of the chord is strummed more than once in the rise and fall of the strumming hand: e 1 1 B 1 1 G 2 2 D 3 3 A 3 3 The chorus is pretty much exactly like the introduction.

title: Wind Of Change chords
author: Wind Of Change – Scorpions
song_information:
WIND OF CHANGE - Scorpions
 Tabbed by: DJ Inferno
  
  
 [Intro]
  
  
  
 [Verse 1]
  
 (  I follow the Moskva
                  Down to Gorky Park
                     Listening to the wind of change
  
 (  An August summer night
                     Soldiers passing by
                     Listening to the wind of change
  
  
 [Interlude]
  
  
  
 [Verse 2]
  
 (  The world is closing in
                 Did you ever think
                        That we could be so close, like brothers
  
 (  The future's in the air
                       I can feel it everywhere
                     Blowing with the wind of change
  
  
 [Chorus]
  
  Take me to the magic of the moment
        On a glory night
            Where the children of tomorrow dream away
   In the wind of change
  
  
 [Verse 3]
  
  Walking down the street
                Distant memories
                      Are buried in the past forever
  
 (  I follow the Moskva
                  Down to Gorky Park
                     Listening to the wind of change
  
  
 [Chorus]
  
 Take me to the magic of the moment
        On a glory night
            Where the children of tomorrow share their dreams
        With you and me
  
 Take me to the magic of the moment
        On a glory night
            Where the children of tomorrow dream away
         In the wind of change
  
  
 [Bridge]
  
  The wind of change blows straight
                    Into the face of time
                             Like a stormwind that will ring
                                The freedom bell for peace of mind
                     Let your balalaika sing
                          What my guitar wants to say
  
  
 [Solo]
  
  
  
  
 [Chorus]
  
 Take me to the magic of the moment
        On a glory night
            Where the children of tomorrow share their dreams
        With you and me
  
 Take me to the magic of the moment
        On a glory night
            Where the children of tomorrow dream away
         In the wind of change
  
  
 [Outro]
  
  
  
 (NOTES)
  
 1) When a chord is followed by a !, it means that you do not strum the chord
 but instead you play it in one quick downward motion.
 2) When a chord is followed by a *, it means that the chord has to be plucked.
 The plucking pattern is given below.
  
 (PLUCKING PATTERN)
  
 The plucking progression for Dm, Am and G goes like this
  
       e|---1-----|---0-----|------------|
 B|-----3---|-----1---|-----3------|
 G|-2-----2-|-2-----2-|-0-----0----|
 D|-0-------|-2-------|-0-------0--|
 A|-0-------|-0-------|-2----------|
 E|-0-------|-0-------|-3----------|
  
 Or this
  
      e|---------|---------|---------|
 B|-6-6-----|-5-5-----|-5-5-----|
 G|-7---7---|-5---5---|-4---4---|
 D|-7-----5-|-7-----7-|-5-----5-|
 A|-5-------|-7-------|-5-------|
 E|---------|-5-------|-3-------|
  
 The whistling bit can be played on the guitar but it doesn't sound too good.
  
 e|----------------------------|
 B|----0-1--1-1-------0-1-3-1--|
 G|--2----------2-2-2----------| x2
 D|----------------------------|
 A|----------------------------|
 E|----------------------------|
  
 The Dm, Am, G plucking is immediately picked up after the last note.
  
 e|-----0-1-0---------------------|
 B|-1-3---------------------------|
 G|-------------------------------|
 D|-------------------------------|
 A|-------------------------------|
 E|-------------------------------|

title: The Weight chords
author: The Weight – The Band
song_information:
[Verse 1]
  
 I pulled in to Nazareth, I was feeling about half past dead.
 I just need some place where I can lay my head.
 "Hey, Mister, can you tell me where a man might find a bed?"
 He just grinned, shook my hand, "No" was all he said.
  
  
 [Chorus]
  
 Take a load off, Fanny.
 Take a load for free.
 Take a load off, Fanny.
 And...And...And.you put the load right on me.
  
  
 [Instrumental]
  
  
  
 [Verse 2]
 I picked up my bag.  I went looking for a place to hide.
 When I saw Carmen and the devil walking side by side.
 I said, "Hey, Carmen, come on. Let's go downtown."
 She said, "I got to go, but my friend can stick around."
  
  
 [Chorus]
  
 Take a load off, Fanny.
 Take a load for free.
 Take a load off, Fanny.
 And...And...And.you put the load right on me.
  
 [Instrumental]
  
  
  
 [Verse 3]
  
 Go down, Miss Moses, there's nothing you can say.
 It's just old Luke, and Luke's waiting on the judgement day.
 "Well, Luke, my friend, what about young Anna Lee?"
 He said, "Do me a favor, son, won't you stay and keep Anna Lee company."
  
  
 [Chorus]
  
 Take a load off, Fanny.
 Take a load for free.
 Take a load off, Fanny.
 And...And...And.you put the load right on me.
  
 [Instrumental]
  
  
  
 [Verse 4]
  
 Crazy Chester followed me and he caught me in the fog.
 He said, "I will fix your rack, if you'll take Jack my dog."
 I said, "Wait a minute, Chester. You know I'm a peaceful man."
 He said, "That's okay, boy.  Won't you feed him when you can?"
  
  
 [Chorus]
  
 Take a load off, Fanny.
 Take a load for free.
 Take a load off, Fanny.
 And...And...And.you put the load right on me.
  
 [Instrumental]
  
  
  
 [Verse 5]
  
 Get your Canonball now, to take me down the line.
 My bag is sinking low, and I do believe it's time
 To get back to Miss Fanny.  You know she's the only one
 Who sent me here with her regards for everyone.
  
  
 [Chorus]
  
 Take a load off, Fanny.
 Take a load for free.
 Take a load off, Fanny.
 And...And...And.you put the load right on me.
  
 [Instrumental]

title: Sign Of The Times chords
author: Sign Of The Times – Harry Styles
song_information:
Artist: Harry Styles
 Song: Sign of the Times
 Key: F major
 Tempo: 60 BPM
 Tuning: E Standard
 Capo: None OR 5th Fret (transpose down 5)
  
 Tabbed by: Matty Sievers
 Email: matty.sievers@gmail.com
 ----------------------------------------------
 Such an amazing song yet so simple!
  
 From the start to the bridge (4:01) it's Fmaj for 1 bar, Dmin for 1 bar and then Cmaj for 2 bars.
 Then from there, the bridge is Fmaj, Dmin, Cmaj and Bbmaj for 1 bar each until 4:49 then it goes back to
 the normal progression for four bars but on those last four, you use the bridge chords.
 So rather than C for two bars before the end on F, it's C and Bb for one bar each.
  
 This will all be in the chords below though; just giving you a basic outline before diving in.
 I'm playing this with no capo as it's fairly easy but if you aren't keen on the Dmin or the Bb
 you can transpose this down by 5, put your capo on 5th and have a fun time playing in the basic
 C fingering postions. That is probably best if your gonna solo this as an acoustic singer and
 need to focus on scrunching your face up when you sing. :P
  
 Edit: Lyrics have been fixed.
  
 Edit #2: Upon closer inspection and a few more sit downs at the piano and the guitar there is most
 certainly a C7 chord in there and have added it in. However, it also sounds fairly good without it so do
 what you are comfortable with.
  
 Chord Voicings, No Capo:
      e|--1-------1------0-----0-----1---------|
 B|--1-------3------1-----1-----3---------|
 G|--2-------2------0-----3-----3---------|
 D|--3-------0------2-----2-----3---------|
 A|--3--------------3-----3-----1---------|
 E|--1------------------------------------|
  
 Chord Voicings, Capo 5th:
       e|---0-----0------3----1-----1-----------|
 B|---1-----1------3----0-----1-----------|
 G|---0-----2------0----0-----2-----------|
 D|---2-----2------0----0-----3-----------|
 A|---3-----0------2----2-----3-----------|
 E|----------------3----3-----1-----------|

title: Youre Beautiful chords
author: Youre Beautiful – James Blunt
song_information:
James Blunt - 'You're Beautiful'
 From 'Back to Bedlam'
  
 A rare tab from Worzell - (Actually my only tab - frustrated at not being able to find
 it anywhere on the internet, I actually bothered to write it down - good song).There's
 two Guitars - Both have a Capo on the 3rd Fret, everything written relative to capo:
  
 Hammer on & Pull off twice on each chord of the verse:
 C  (hammer on & pull off on the D string)
 G  (hammer on & pull off on the A string)
 Am (hammer on & pull off on the D string)
 F  (hammer on & pull off on the G string)

 My life is brilliant.
 My love is pure.
 I saw an angel,
 Of that I'm sure.

 La la la la, la la la la, la la la la, la

title: The Boxer chords
author: The Boxer – Simon & Garfunkel
song_information:
Tune down your guitar one semi-tone. The studio recording is tuned slightly sharp of a
 half step down. Try about +20 cents using an electronic tuner.
  
 If you want to play in the original key in standard tuning, transpose this chord sheet
 and/or use a capo to match the recording:
  
 Transpose  Capo       Play   Key
 -3         2nd fret   A      B   (studio version)
 -5         4th fret   G      B   (studio version)

title: Fake Plastic Trees chords
author: Fake Plastic Trees – Radiohead
song_information:
Strumming pattern:
  
 e----------------------| (only strum for the D5 chord)
 B----------x-----------|
 G----------x-----------|
 D---x-x----x-----------|
 A---x-x----x-----------| (for the D5 chord, don't play this string...)
 E--don't play----------|
  
 You can also alternate using the E string on chords A and D5
  
 Start strumming A for the intro, come in with
  
 [Verse 1]
  
 Her green plastic watering can
            For her fake chinese rubber plant
                In the fake plastic earth
 That she bought from a rubber man
             In a town full of rubber plans
         To get rid of itself
  
  
 [Chorus]
  
               It wears her out..
               It wears her out..
               It wears her out..
               It wears her out
  
  
 [Verse 2]
  
 She lives with a broken man
          A cracked polystyrene man 
            Who just crumbles and burns
 He used to do surgery
          For girls in the eighties
              But gravity always wins
  
  
 [Chorus]
  
              It wears him out..
               It wears him out..
               It wears him out..
               It weaaaaaaarrrs
  
  
 [Verse 3]
  
 She looks like the real thing
           She tastes like the real thing
            My fake plastic love
 But I can't help the feeling
            I could blow through the ceiling
             If I just turn and run
  
  
 [Chorus]
  
              It wears me out..
              It wears me out..
              It wears me out..
              It wears me out
  
  
 [Outro]
  
                 And if I could be who you wanted
             If I could be who you wanted
         All the time..
         All the time..
  
 [Outro]

I'd always hoped for better, Thought maybe together you and me would find it, I got no plans, I ain't going nowhere, so take your fast car and keep on driving. title: 22 chords
author: 22 – Taylor Swift
song_information:
***Note***
 In Taylor's acoustic version she plays her G as
 Gsus2 [300033], and the Cadd9 as Csus2 [x30033].
 I'm NOT changing the chord names throughout because
 playing what I have sounds the same, whether
 playing along with her live version or the CD
 track.  Link to her live acoustic version -
  
 Youtube link: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KbQYFMsHJzw
  
  
           *******IMPORTANT NOTE ;)*******
 THE CHORDS IN THE CHORUS WITH THE *'S ARE JUST ONE STRUM
 OR BEAT AND THEN RIGHT INTO THE NEXT CHORD!  IT'S TRICKY!
 PLAY ALONG WITH THE SONG TO GET THE TIMING DOWN. AFTER
 A FEW TRIES ALONG WITH THE SONG, YOU'LL BE A PRO!!
  
 Thanks to UG member Calc1o for nicely pointing out a
 missing Dsus4 in the chorus :)
  
  
 Send in your guitar chords song request @ www.liveloveguitar.com

 No Capo
